{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ed38329e-ae11-4028-a174-a2868c0df474","content":"Here are the common options depending on your stack:\n\n**ASP.NET Core (dotnet)**\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth Individual    # Identity-based (JWT Bearer)\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg     # Microsoft Entra ID (Azure AD)\ndotnet new webapi --auth MultiOrg      # Multi-tenant Azure AD\ndotnet new webapi --auth Windows       # Windows/Negotiate auth\n```\n\n**Node.js / Express** — Use libraries like `passport.js`, `jsonwebtoken`, or `express-oauth2-jwt-bearer` with frameworks like Express or Fastify.\n\n**Python / FastAPI** — Use `python-jose` for JWT, `authlib` for OAuth2, or FastAPI's built-in `OAuth2PasswordBearer`.\n\n**Authentication approaches:**\n| Method | Best For |\n|---|---|\n| **JWT Bearer** | SPAs, mobile apps, microservices |\n| **OAuth2 / OpenID Connect** | Third-party login (Google, GitHub) |\n| **API Keys** | Simple service-to-service |\n| **Cookie-based** | Server-rendered web apps |\n\nWould you like me to scaffold a project with a specific stack and auth method?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b4a5707e-56d8-4528-b732-15df6d9f7d1b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking a general knowledge question about web API project templates and authentication options. This doesn't require any tool calls - it's a straightforward question I can answer from my knowledge.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer about common web API templates and authentication options.","outputTokens":356,"requestId":"2813:4D842:119019:172AEB:69FFD740"},"id":"ac410e01-4ae3-4af7-87c8-f7c5203c43f0","timestamp":"2026-05-10T00:54:32.199Z","parentId":"83313328-4499-40a3-bc38-75b3fe70b5f2"}
